  "text": "To facilitate the detection of cryptic species, we investigated haplotype distribution among species using Arlequin 3.5 [CITATION_1] . Sequences from all the individual worms were included in the Arlequin analysis, and all nucleotide sites with missing data were excluded. We determined the number of unique haplotypes in each species (for both the ITS and cox-1 regions) and investigated the phylogenetic relationships between these haplotypes in MEGA 5.0, using the same phylogeny construction methods described previously.",
